-- в”Ђв”Ђ Bismuth в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ
UPDATE tools SET
  short_description = COALESCE($q$Bismuth was a free, open-source tiling window manager add-on for the KDE Plasma desktop on Linux; the project was archived in June 2024 after KDE Plasma added native tiling support.$q$, short_description),
  pricing_model = COALESCE($q$open-source$q$, pricing_model),
  starting_price = COALESCE($q$Free$q$, starting_price),
  founded_year = COALESCE(NULL, founded_year),
  company_size = COALESCE($q$Open-source community project maintained by volunteer contributors, not a company$q$, company_size),
  headquarters = COALESCE(NULL, headquarters),
  languages = ARRAY[$q$English$q$]::text[],
  seo_title = COALESCE($q$Bismuth: Free KDE Plasma Tiling Window Manager (Archived)$q$, seo_title),
  seo_meta_description = COALESCE($q$Bismuth was an open-source tiling window manager add-on for KDE Plasma, similar to i3 or dwm. See its features, install steps, and archived status.$q$, seo_meta_description),
  llm_readable_summary = COALESCE($q$Bismuth was a free, open-source tiling window manager add-on for the KDE Plasma desktop environment on Linux, designed to automatically arrange open windows into tiled layouts and let users manage them via keyboard shortcuts, in a style similar to i3, Sway, or dwm. It was created as a fork of an earlier project called Krohnkite, after Krohnkite's original maintainer had been inactive for more than a year; Bismuth carried the same core tiling functionality forward while adding its own configuration module and additional features. The project integrated natively with KDE Plasma features such as Virtual Desktops and Activities, supported multiple switchable tiling layouts for different workflows, and included a custom border-only window decoration styled for tiling use. It required KDE Plasma 5.20 or later, Qt 5.15 or later, and KDE Frameworks 5.78 or later, and was packaged for installation on major Linux distributions including Ubuntu and Debian (via apt install kwin-bismuth), Fedora (via dnf install bismuth), Arch Linux (via the AUR), and community or official packages on Solus, openSUSE, and Gentoo. The project was hosted on GitHub under the Bismuth-Forge organization, grew to roughly 2,400 GitHub stars and 96 forks, and was supported in part through community donations via Open Collective. In June 2024, specifically on June 16, 2024, the Bismuth-Forge/bismuth repository was archived by its owner and made read-only, effectively ending active development. This followed KDE Plasma's introduction of native, built-in tiling window management starting with Plasma 5.27, which added first-party APIs and a polished tiling user experience directly in the desktop environment, reducing the practical need for a third-party extension like Bismuth. As of 2026, Bismuth is best understood as a historically significant but now-unmaintained open-source project; it remains free and its source code and past distro packages are still publicly available, but it receives no further updates or bug fixes, and users on modern KDE Plasma releases are generally directed toward Plasma's native tiling feature instead of installing Bismuth.$q$, llm_readable_summary),
  status = 'published',
  noindex = false,
  sitemap_eligible = true,
  published_at = COALESCE(published_at, now()),
  updated_at = now()
WHERE id = 'fd499a7e-95e4-4f5b-9e0d-e56389d69a77';

