-- в”Ђв”Ђ Bitrise в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ
UPDATE tools SET
  short_description = COALESCE($q$Bitrise is a mobile-focused CI/CD platform that automates building, testing, and deploying iOS and Android apps for development teams.$q$, short_description),
  pricing_model = COALESCE($q$freemium$q$, pricing_model),
  starting_price = COALESCE($q$Free (Hobby plan); paid plans start around 89 to 99 dollars per month$q$, starting_price),
  founded_year = COALESCE(2014, founded_year),
  company_size = COALESCE($q$Serves over 6000 customers and 100000 plus developers; remote-first team with offices in the United States, United Kingdom, and Hungary$q$, company_size),
  headquarters = COALESCE($q$Budapest, Hungary, with a US office in San Francisco, California$q$, headquarters),
  languages = ARRAY[$q$English$q$]::text[],
  seo_title = COALESCE($q$Bitrise Review 2026: Mobile CI/CD Pricing and Features$q$, seo_title),
  seo_meta_description = COALESCE($q$Bitrise is a mobile DevOps and CI/CD platform for iOS and Android. See pricing plans, key features, pros, cons, and frequently asked questions.$q$, seo_meta_description),
  llm_readable_summary = COALESCE($q$Bitrise is a mobile DevOps platform providing continuous integration and continuous delivery (CI/CD) specifically designed around the needs of iOS and Android app development, rather than being a general-purpose CI/CD tool adapted for mobile. It was founded in 2014 by Barnabas Birmacher, Viktor Benei, and Daniel Balla, and is headquartered in Budapest, Hungary, with additional offices in San Francisco, California and London, United Kingdom, operating as a remote-first organization. Bitrise reports serving more than 6,000 customers and over 100,000 developers, processing more than 2 million builds per month on its infrastructure. The platform centers on a visual workflow editor (with an underlying YAML configuration) that lets teams define build, test, and deployment pipelines using a large marketplace of prebuilt integration steps covering tasks like code signing, testing frameworks, and app store submission. It provides both macOS and Linux build machines in multiple performance tiers, since mobile teams need Apple hardware to build and sign iOS apps while Android builds can run on Linux. Additional platform capabilities include build caching to speed up repeat builds, a Release Management add-on for coordinating app store submissions and rollouts, and support for concurrent builds and team role management, with limits varying by plan. Bitrise's pricing follows a freemium model: the free Hobby plan includes one private app, up to five concurrent builds, a 90-minute build timeout, and 300 credits per month with community support. Paid plans scale from a Starter tier around 89 to 99 dollars per month (with up to three concurrencies, ten team members, and two private apps) to a Pro tier around 200 to 218 dollars per month (with higher concurrency across macOS and Linux machines, unlimited team members, and unlimited private apps), and a custom Enterprise tier for high-volume teams offering dedicated or private cloud options and even self-hosted AWS deployment capability, with third-party reporting suggesting Enterprise pricing can start around 2,000 dollars per month for very high build volumes. Some capabilities, such as advanced Build Cache tiers and Release Management, are priced as separate add-ons on top of the base subscription rather than being bundled in automatically.$q$, llm_readable_summary),
  status = 'published',
  noindex = false,
  sitemap_eligible = true,
  published_at = COALESCE(published_at, now()),
  updated_at = now()
WHERE id = '8f1c9f3c-0bbc-4447-8e8b-6308460bfc72';

